The website VeriTrade is used to allow users to verify buyers and sellers that trade on C2C E-commerce platforms.
The website allows users to select between wether they are a buyer or a seller, and then navigate to a page to enter respective details.

Sellers:
-> Enter their personal information and which sites they trade on 
-> Recieve OTP on creating new profile for themselves
-> Enter seller into database for buyer search
    - Display user feedback form buyers 


Buyers:
-> Enter details of seller to recieve a trust score (0-100):
    - Seller phone number
    - Email
    - Social handle (IG/TikTok/Facebook profile URL)
    - Business name
    - Bank account holder name (optional)
    - Marketplace profile link
    - OTP pin sent to seller 
    - Registered user on VeriTrade
-> Score reflects a prompted message of Risk category: Low / Medium / High
-> User can search for specific seller by username if they are a registered user of VeriTrade or phone number/email to see previous purchase user feedback
-> User feedback on purchases for other users to view and get relative purchasing advice



